<h2>Create a new work item</h2>

<p>To create a new work item in COMPASS, follow these steps:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Work reporting</strong> from the left sidebar menu</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Create entry</strong> button at the top right of the page (this button is only visible if you have admin permissions)</li>
    <li>Fill in the required work item information:
        <ul>
            <li>Work item title (required)</li>
            <li>Work item code (optional)</li>
            <li>Start date and target delivery date</li>
            <li>Phase</li>
            <li>Business area</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> to save your work item</li>
</ol>

<h3>What happens next?</h3>
<p>Once created, you can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Add team members</li>
    <li>Set the RAG status</li>
    <li>Add milestones, risks, and issues</li>
    <li>Complete additional work item information</li>
</ul>

<p>For more information, see the <a href="@Url.Action("Details", "Documentation", new { id = "project-enhancements" })">Work documentation</a>.</p>

